The surface of the silica-coated gold nanoparticles GNPSi7, GNPSi9 and GNPSi13 were decorated with a controlled amount of PDI, determined by separating the unreacted PDI by centrifugation, and measuring the absorption spectra of the PDI-labelled nanoparticles in ethanol. For the PDI-labelled SiNPs, the spectrum corresponds to the sum of the SiNPs scattering and the absorption of surface-attached PDI. We correct for light scattering, by subtracting the spectra of unlabelled SiNPs of the same size (which corresponds to the inverse fourth power of the wavelength due to scattering) matched for the same scattering intensity (Fig. S9 - Supporting Information), and calculated the PDI concentration using the molar extinction coefficient of PDI in ethanol at 22 °C (ε22521nm\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
